  "text": "It is well established that considering the raw scores from actual recognition algorithms as feature vectors for machine learning-based postrecognition score analysis, as we did with our statistical meta-recognition, generally does not work [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] . An explanation for this is provided in Section V. Thus, we define a set of features in accordance with [CITATION_4] - [CITATION_5] , [CITATION_6] , and [CITATION_7] . We derive each feature from the distance measurements or similarity scores produced by the recognition algorithm. Before we calculate each feature, we sort the scores from best to worst. The top scores are used for the feature vector generation. We consider three different feature classes.",
